    The tagged list representation for names
    includes the tag "name" as first
    element and the string representing the name as second element.

	  \begin{eqnarray*}
	  \ll \textit{name} \gg & = &
	  \texttt{list("name", }\textit{symbol}\texttt{)}
	  \end{eqnarray*}

	where $\textit{symbol}$ is a string
	that contains the characters that make up the
	$\textit{name}$ as written in the program.
	The syntax predicate for names is 
	is_name.

	      variable
	      variable_example
	      tagged_list

function is_name(component) {
    return is_tagged_list(component, "name");
}


